                <note rend="inline" type="source">701.6193/84: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-08-19T18:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 19, 1926—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>168. Your telegram number 331 of August 18th, noon. The question of the Soviet
                    Ambassador’s status concerns only China and the Soviet Government. No doubt as
                    to this fact should be left in the minds of the Chinese.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harrison</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
